  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesized that mesenchymal stem cells can be isolated from fracture
      site, iliac crest, and tibial crest, and can be expanded to be used in the management of
      nonunion fracture.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
